The Chairman of the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, Prof. Mahmood Yakubu, has ruled out political or financial influence in the postponement of the Presidential and National Assembly elections earlier scheduled to hold today and the governorship, states assemblies and FCT Area Council election slated for March 2, 2019. The INEC boss disclosed this on Saturday at the National Election Collation Centre located at the International Conference Centre (ICC), Abuja, while addressing stakeholders. According to him: “The decision has nothing to do with security, political influence or inadequate resources”. Details soon They are trying to sabotage our efforts, INEC chairman cries out Re-run elections: Rivers political warlords return to trenches 2019: INEC warns incumbents against using state resources